#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:7
msgid "Design rationale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:9
msgid ""
"ISP configuration parameters and statistics are processed and collected by "
"drivers and exchanged with userspace through data types that usually reflect "
"the ISP peripheral registers layout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:13
msgid ""
"Each ISP driver defines its own metadata output format for parameters and a "
"metadata capture format for statistics. The buffer layout is realized by a "
"set of C structures that reflects the registers layout. The number and types "
"of C structures is fixed by the format definition and becomes part of the "
"Linux kernel uAPI/uABI interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:19
msgid ""
"Because of the hard requirement of backward compatibility when extending the "
"user API/ABI interface, modifying an ISP driver capture or output metadata "
"format after it has been accepted by mainline is very hard if not impossible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:23
msgid ""
"It generally happens, in fact, that after the first accepted revision of an "
"ISP driver the buffers layout need to be modified, either to support new "
"hardware blocks, to fix bugs or to support different revisions of the "
"hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:27
msgid ""
"Each of these situations would require defining a new metadata format, "
"making it really hard to maintain and extend drivers and requiring userspace "
"to use the correct format depending on the kernel revision in use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:32
msgid "V4L2 ISP configuration parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:34
msgid ""
"For these reasons, Video4Linux2 defines generic types for ISP configuration "
"parameters and statistics. Drivers are still expected to define their own "
"formats for their metadata output and capture nodes, but the buffers layout "
"can be defined using the extensible and versioned types defined by include/"
"uapi/linux/media/v4l2-isp.h."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:40
msgid ""
"Drivers are expected to provide the definitions of their supported ISP "
"blocks and the expected maximum size of a buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/media/v4l2-isp.rst:43
msgid ""
"For driver developers a set of helper functions to assist them with "
"validation of the buffer received from userspace is available in drivers/"
"media/v4l2-core/v4l2-isp.c"
msgstr ""

